<item>
            <title>[SPARK-15262] race condition in killing an executor and reregistering an executor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15262</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a race condition when killing an executor and reregistering an executor happen at the same time. Here is the execution steps to reproduce it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. master find a worker is dead&lt;br/&gt;
2. master tells driver to remove executor&lt;br/&gt;
3. driver remove executor&lt;br/&gt;
4. BlockManagerMasterEndpoint remove the block manager&lt;br/&gt;
5. executor finds it&apos;s not reigstered via heartbeat&lt;br/&gt;
6. executor send reregister block manager&lt;br/&gt;
7. register block manager&lt;br/&gt;
8. executor is killed by worker&lt;br/&gt;
9. CoarseGrainedSchedulerBackend ignores onDisconnected as this address is not in the executor list&lt;br/&gt;
10. BlockManagerMasterEndpoint.blockManagerInfo contains dead block managers&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As BlockManagerMasterEndpoint.blockManagerInfo contains some dead block managers, when we unpersist a RDD, remove a broadcast, or clean a shuffle block via a RPC endpoint of a dead block manager, we will get ClosedChannelException.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
